<DOC><DOCNO> AP880412-0014 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-12-88 0034EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--China-Soviets     04-12 0140</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--China-Soviets,0144</SECOND><HEAD>China Hoping To Increase Trade With Soviet Union</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   China, hoping to increase trade with the SovietUnion and Eastern Europe, has set up five new trade ports and planseight more, the official China Daily newspaper said today.   China says it has a large surplus of labor, arable land andindustrial commodities but is short of timber, electricity andfertilizer.   The Soviet Union suffers shortages of labor, agriculturalproducts and light industrial and textile products but has goodsupplies of timber, coal and petroleum, the paper said.   Presently, China has only three trade ports, all in Heilongjiangprovince, bordering the Soviet Union.   The State Council has given provincial authorities the power toapprove its own export projects, to set up barter trade, to set upjoint projects with the Soviets and to exchange technology.</TEXT></DOC>